Description:
LAST ONE IN THIS FANTASTIC SPOT! APPROX. HALF AN ACRE IN THE HEART OF DRYSDALE.
Walk to the village, schools, parklands and all medical facilities. Lake Lorne and the Rail Trail within walking distance, bike track as well as leisure activities, all so very close. This block will provide so many options to the new owner, light filled backyard will enable a solar passive design with ease. The Bellarine is a beautiful spot to live, nestled amongst hills, vineyards, restaurants and the magic of the bay, a short drive to Geelong, another hour to Melbourne and the Great Ocean Road. Please call me to speak further, do not expect this unique opportunity to linger.

Description:
Motivated Vendor Keen to Negotiate
The property is located on the out skirts of Drysdale adjacent to the farming hinterland. The views across the township of Drysdale to Curlewis, Corio Bay and Geelong are nothing but spectacular. The home is surrounded by established trees and immaculate gardens which create a very calming retreat. For those who love the outdoors a hit of tennis on your own court is a luxury.
The home is inviting and spacious with the main living areas taking advantage of the beautiful views. There are three bedrooms downstairs, a second living area or study and main bathroom. Upstairs you can retreat to the architecturally designed parents area with floor to ceiling windows and private ensuite with spa.
Ample shedding and two horse yards or future orchard complete the package. This property is perfect for a tradesman's storage requirements.
Inspection a must. Reasonable offers considered.
Rhonda Humpage : 0457 313 609

Description:
STEP BACK IN TIME!
Lets take a journey back in time to the 70's because that is what you will find at this recently listed home in Drysdale.
Drysdale is a country town 20 minutes from the city of Geelong, surf beaches, boat ramps to put the fishing boat in the water, restaurants, wineries, bike trails, sporting groups, shopping and medical centres not to mention the choice of four Primary Schools and three High Schools.
This very solid home comprises formal lounge with open fire place and bar, great for entertaining in the winter months. Formal dining overlooking a private courtyard. Kitchen meals where stepping outside is the potential to enhance the outdoor BBQ area.
Three bedrooms all with BIRs main bedroom with semi ensuite. The original double garage has been converted to a large rumpus room but would lend itself to being used as a home office if required. A stand alone double garage was built with a large workshop at the rear. But wait there's more, a massive shed hidden from the view where the man of the house can be contacted via intercom to be called in for dinner.
Back in the day this home also had a swimming pool that has been filled in but the fencing still remains.
If the 70's are not your thing you can set about changing this home to suit your own personal taste. Do you have a bit of vision? Then book a time with me to show you around.

Stylish modern cottage
First open house this Saturday. Offering privacy from the street with a quaint cottage feel is this delightful three bedroom, two bathroom family home. With a welcoming verandah protecting the home from the northerly summer sun.
The living room has vaulted ceilings giving a sense of space.
Galley style kitchen & dining area overlooking the garden.
Master bedroom with ensuite.
A large stand alone double garage with separate roller doors.
There is ample backyard & the drive is lined with hedge rows. Established gardens offering privacy & tranquility.
Perfect for those seeking to be close to all the amenities, schools, shopping centre & cafes.
This property has the location, price & style.
Just a heartbeat away from the Drysdale Township Shopping Centre. Close to Early Learning Child Care, McLeod's Waterholes & primary schools.

Description:
Rural Haven and Horse Heaven
Established to surpass average equestrian requirements, this 16 ha – 40 acres approx semi-rural lifestyle property centres around a modern four bedroom homestead.
Set in glorious gardens, its solid exterior encloses a cleverly designed passive solar family habitat. Verandahs spanning front and rear allow only winter sunshine to penetrate the welcoming interior, and excellent cross ventilation means no augmented cooling is required.
Double-sided wood heaters set in a brick heat-bank keep two large living areas snug. Adorned with timber corbels and leadlight cabinets, the country-sized kitchen contains all mod cons such as dishwasher and glass-top hob.
Family bathroom with corner spa services three big bedrooms. Generous main has en suite and walk-in robe.
Massive 18×9 metre partitioned shed contains removable stables to allow conversion for conventional use. Attached tack-room and feed storage room, holding pens, hot water washing area, 15 paddocks, cattle yards & town water is connected.
Surprisingly peaceful, it's just up the street from an extensive and comprehensive list of shops, schools and services at Drysdale, around 10 minutes to Ocean Grove and surf beaches, 20 minutes into Geelong and about 90 minutes to Melbourne. Wineries, beaches, Adventure Park, koala sanctuary, cosy cafes, renowned restaurants and much more are also here on the Bellarine. So whether for ponies or peace, this property is simply the ultimate combination of convenience and a tranquil lifestyle.

Established to surpass average equestrian requirements, this 16 ha – 40 acres approx semi-rural lifestyle property centres around a modern four bedroom homestead.
Set in glorious gardens, its solid exterior encloses a cleverly designed passive solar family habitat. Verandahs spanning front and rear allow only winter sunshine to penetrate the welcoming interior, and excellent cross ventilation means no augmented cooling is required.
Double-sided wood heaters set in a brick heat-bank keep two large living areas snug. Adorned with timber corbels and leadlight cabinets, the country-sized kitchen contains all mod cons such as dishwasher and glass-top hob.
Family bathroom with corner spa services three big bedrooms. Generous main has en suite and walk-in robe.
Massive 18×9 metre partitioned shed contains removable stables to allow conversion for conventional use. Attached tack-room and feed storage room, holding pens, hot water washing area, 15 paddocks, cattle yards & town water is connected.
Surprisingly peaceful, it's just up the street from an extensive and comprehensive list of shops, schools and services at Drysdale, around 10 minutes to Ocean Grove and surf beaches, 20 minutes into Geelong and about 90 minutes to Melbourne. Wineries, beaches, Adventure Park, koala sanctuary, cosy cafes, renowned restaurants and much more are also here on the Bellarine. So whether for ponies or peace, this property is simply the ultimate combination of convenience and a tranquil lifestyle.

Description:
Centrally located town house
This three bedroom modern townhouse is centrally located to the town centre. In almost new condition this residence has been immaculately maintained. Featuring a stacked stone facade entry.
Open plan kitchen, living & dining with stainless steel appliances and gas hotplates. Ample bench space with pot draws & overhead cupboard.
Master bedroom with ensuite & walk in robe.
Private passageway servicing second & third bedrooms with built in bedrooms, central bathroom & laundry.
Secluded low maintenance courtyard with double sliding door access from the living area.
Garage with remote roller door & secure internal access.
The design is functional & would suit those still wanting the feeling on a larger house but with out the hassle of a large backyard
Just a short stroll to the Drysdale Shopping village, public & private primary schools, bowls, croquet & tennis clubs.

Description:
Modern Family Home in Enviable Location
This executive family home is positioned in the best location Drysdale could possible offer and in the heart of the Bellarine - enclosed amongst the lake and walking tracks, Rail Trail and located within 5 minutes of the Drysdale township, local amenities, sporting facilities and golf courses. Just a 20 minute drive to the Geelong CBD and waterfront provides the lazy rural lifestyle close to all the action. Just 8 years new with all the custom fit out and extras you would expect from a classic family entertainer - 4 excellent sized bedrooms, 3 with WIRs, enormous master with complete ensuite. The home was built with entertaining at the forefront, offering 3 living options. Formal lounge is oversized, whilst also offering separate rumpus/billiard room ideal for teenagers' retreat. Also open plan deluxe kitchen with glass splash back, stone benches and modern appliances. Huge butler's pantry is the perfect compliment. Large dining area and also 3rd possible family room alternative. Outdoor provides secure and spacious backyard with cracking undercover alfresco entertaining area for BBQs all year around. The clever house design provides double remote garage, plus an extra single lock up garage ideal for tradespeople, boat/caravan or workshop area with further off-street double gates for extra storage or back yard access. With central gas heating, and positioned on a beautiful block just under 1000sqm. Perfect family living in irreplaceable location - You better be quick!

Description:
Community Living - In Comfort!
This is your opportunity to live in a modern townhouse and experience the advantages the community living aspect this property has to offer. Situated at the end of Marsh Court, this rear unit will allow the new occupants freedom to engage with neighbours or enjoy the privacy beyond the fence.
Recently constructed, the home boasts 3 bedrooms, all with built in robes and the master bedroom sports a large ensuite. The showers in both ensuite and bathroom have room to move. Open plan kitchen, dining and living areas support the home and the spotted gum floors are hard wearing and define the area. Heating through a cosy stand-alone gas fire and climate controlled comfort throughout the home. The kitchen will become the hub of this home and the appliances are hardly used. Double garage with remote allows internal access to the living areas. Comfort, quality and location all mean that this townhouse is well worth an inspection and requires your attention today!

Description:
Prestigious Bellarine Peninsula
Situated on 80 Acres (32.37 Ha) of prime undulating productive country, and commanding magnificent panoramic Bay Views to Mornington Peninsula & Port Phillip Heads, this elevated allotment holds unlimited potential for future home sites, or to build your dream residence (S.T.C.A).
